OL,3,COfwat planning independent monitor for
OL,4,CThames Water after ratings downgrades
OL,6,FOfwat also proposed #168 million of
OL,7,Ffines for three of England's biggest
OL,8,Fwater companies for failing to manage
OL,9,Fsewage spills, including a #104
OL,10,Fmillion penalty for Thames.
OL,12,FThe fine for Thames came alongside a
OL,13,F#47 million penalty for Yorkshire
OL,14,FWater and #17 million for Northumbrian
OL,15,FWater, as the first batch of results
OL,16,Ffrom its biggest ever investigation
OL,17,Finto the industry.
